'''Paik Seung-ho''' ({{Korean|hangul=백승호}}; born 17 March 1997) is a South Korean professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[central midfielder]] for {{English football updater|BirmingC}} club [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] and the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]].

==Early life==
[[File:2012 2013 - Seungho-Paik - Flickr - Castroquini-FCB.jpg|thumb|upright|right|Paik in 2012]]
In 2009, as a member of [[Seoul]] Daedong Elementary School, he played 18 games in the Elementary Weekend League and scored 30 goals. Since then, he has received attention as an outstanding prospect, winning the 22nd [[Cha Bum-kun]] Football Grand Prize. In December, he participated in the 1st [[Copa Catalunya|Korea-Catalonia Youth Cup]] in Barcelona, Spain as a member of the South Korean national under-14 football team,<ref>{{Cite web |script-title=ko:유소년축구 대표, 스페인 카탈루냐컵 출전 |url=https://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&oid=001&aid=0003003107&sid1=001 |access-date=13 April 2021 |website=[[Naver]] |language=ko}}</ref> and was offered a contract as a result of his impressive performance.<ref>{{Cite web |date=28 January 2019 |script-title=ko:6년 만에 흩어진 바르사 3총사…"정상에서 만나자" |url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20170830037700007?input=1195m |access-date=13 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190128135809/https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20170830037700007?input=1195m |archive-date=28 January 2019 |publisher=[[Yonhap News Agency]]}}</ref> However, he was already scouted by Maetan Middle School, [[Suwon Samsung Bluewings Academy|a youth team of Samsung Bluewings]] in [[Suwon]], and was scheduled to enter, but Samsung Bluewings decided to send Paik to Spain with a long-term vision and also to support him.<ref>{{Cite web |publisher=Osen |date=27 June 2012 |script-title=ko:"수원 이겨라" 바르샤 유스 백승호, 빅버드 찾아 '응원' |url=http://mosen.mt.co.kr/article/G1109424047 |access-date=13 April 2021 |language=ko}}</ref>

Paik played for Maetan Middle School, the under-15 team of the Suwon Samsung Bluewings, until March 2010, before moving to Barcelona's under-13 team, Infantil A, in April 2010. In July 2011, Paik signed a five-year contract with Barcelona's youth team, leaving him in Barcelona's uniform until the age of 19.<ref>{{Cite web|date=6 July 2011|script-title=ko:'축구신동' 백승호, 바르셀로나 유소년팀과 5년 계약|url=https://www.hankyung.com/sports/article/2011070628617|access-date=13 April 2021|publisher=[[The Korea Economic Daily]]|language=ko}}</ref> However, in February 2013, [[FIFA]] suspended six players, including Paik, from Barcelona's youth team, for violating Article 19 of the [[FIFA rules]]<ref>{{Cite web|last=Kim|first=Yeong-rok|date=25 February 2013|script-title=ko:'바르샤 코리안' 적신호…이승우 이어 백승호-장결희도 출전금지|url=https://sports.donga.com/3/all/20130225/53281791/2|website=Sports Donga}}</ref> so he could not participate in Barcelona's official matches until January 2016, when the disciplinary action was released. He then played actively for Barcelona Juvenile A, and made his professional debut on 21 February, as a substitute in [[Segunda División B]] match with [[Atlético Levante UD|Atlético Levante]] in the 45th minute of the second half.<ref>{{Cite web |publisher=Osen |date=21 February 2016 |script-title=ko:백승호, 바르사 B 공식 데뷔 |url=http://mosen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110357430 |access-date=13 April 2021 |language=ko}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Girona===
Paik played for Barcelona as a youth player for seven years, but he had difficulty competing in the senior team. He joined [[Girona FC|Girona]] on 21 July 2017, and played for [[CF Peralada|Peralada]], the reserve team of Girona at the time, in the Segunda División B during his first professional season.

Paik made his first team debut against [[Atlético Madrid]] in the [[Copa del Rey]] on 10 January 2019.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2019/01/11/2019011101258.html |title=Paik Seung-ho Debuts in Spain's Top-Tier League |publisher=[[The Chosun Ilbo]] |date=11 January 2019}}</ref> He made his [[La Liga]] debut as a substitute against Barcelona on 27 January. He officially played six matches for Girona excluding a [[Supercopa de Catalunya]] match.<ref name="soccerway"/>

===Darmstadt 98===
On 31 August 2019, Paik signed for [[2. Bundesliga]] side [[SV Darmstadt 98|Darmstadt 98]] on a three-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sv98.de/home/lilien/aktuelles/details/news/sv-98-verpflichtet-seung-ho-paik/?tx_news_pi1%5Bcontroller%5D=News&tx_news_pi1%5Baction%5D=detail&cHash=24d4b9d40dea99e294991854c35bcd3e|title=SV 98 verpflichtet Seung-Ho Paik|language=German|publisher=SV Darmstadt 98|date=31 August 2019|access-date=31 August 2019}}</ref> He played for Darmstadt for one and a half years, but his status in the team was gradually lowered. He eventually considered a return to his country in order to get more appearances in the field and moreover participate in the [[Football at the 2020 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2020 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.starnewskorea.com/stview.php?no=2021030421000909987 |script-title=ko:‘배신자’ 낙인찍힌 백승호, 다름슈타트로 돌아가지도 못한다 |language=ko |publisher=Starnews Korea |date=4 March 2021 |access-date=3 October 2023}}</ref>

=== Jeonbuk Hyundai Motors ===
In March 2021, he signed for [[K League 1]] club [[Jeonbuk Hyundai Motors]].<ref>{{cite news |date=30 March 2021 |title=Seung-Ho Paik verlässt den SV Darmstadt 98 Richtung Südkorea |url=https://www.kicker.de/paik-verlaesst-den-sv-darmstadt-richtung-suedkorea-801039/artikel |access-date=30 March 2021 |work=kicker |language=de}}</ref> Within the three years of his career, he won the league and domestic cup titles, in 2021 and 2022 respectively.

===Birmingham City===
After the end of his three-year contract with Jeonbuk and his exemption from mandatory military service as an Asian Games gold medalist, Paik was expected to return to Europe.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/2024-01-02/sports/football/Europe-could-come-calling-for-Paik-Seungho-this-January/1948934 |title=Europe could come calling for Paik Seung-ho this January |first=Jim |last=Bulley |newspaper=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]] |date=2 January 2024 |access-date=30 January 2024}}</ref> He joined [[EFL Championship]] club [[Birmingham City F.C.|Birmingham City]] on 30 January 2024.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bcfc.com/news/all/paik-seung-ho-is-a-blue |title=Paik Seung-ho is a blue! |publisher=Birmingham City F.C. |date=29 January 2024 |access-date=30 January 2024}}</ref> On 4 May 2024, the final match day of the [[2023–24 EFL Championship|EFL Championship season]], Paik scored his first goal for Birmingham in a 1–0 win over [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]], though the victory was not enough to save the team from relegation.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/clke3rznglet |title=Birmingham City 1–0 Norwich City |first=Ged |last=Scott |publisher=BBC Sport |date=4 May 2024 |access-date=8 May 2024}}</ref>

Paik remained at Birmingham the next season, playing at the [[EFL League One]]. His skills were assessed as being above League One level,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://footballleagueworld.co.uk/birmingham-city-praised-for-retaining-seung-ho-paik/ |title="Really surprised" – Claim made on Seung-Ho Paik's Birmingham City situation after Leeds United talk |publisher=Football League World |date=2024-09-03 |access-date=2025-04-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/birmingham-city-player-ratings-barnsley-31361415 |title=Birmingham City player ratings after 6–2 Barnsley rout tees up promotion party |publisher=Birmingham Live |date=2025-04-05 |access-date=2025-04-14}}</ref> and helped the club promote to the Championship easily.<ref name="league1">{{cite news |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11694/13346982/birmingham-city-crowned-league-one-champions-days-after-securing-promotion-to-championship |title=Birmingham City crowned League One champions days after securing promotion to Championship |publisher=Sky Sports |date=2025-04-12 |access-date=2025-04-14}}</ref> The club earned triple-digit points as they won the League One title, and he was one of their seven members to be selected for the [[PFA Team of the Year (2020s)#League One 6|PFA Team of the Year]].<ref name="pfa">{{cite web |url=https://www.thepfa.com/news/2025/8/19/pfa-league-one-team-of-the-year-2025 |title=PFA League One Team of the Year 2025 |publisher=Professional Footballers' Association |date=2025-08-19 |access-date=2025-08-21}}</ref>

==International career==
Paik made his [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]] debut on 11 June 2019 in a friendly against Iran, as a starter.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=539548|title=South Korea v Iran game report|date=11 June 2019}}</ref>

Paik played South Korea's round-of-16 match against [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] as a substitute in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], and his goal in the match was nominated for goal of the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/fifaplus/en/articles/world-cup-qatar-2022-vote-now-hyundai-goal-of-the-tournament-al-dawsari-richarlison-gakpo-fernandez-aboubakar-chavez-mbappe-paik-neymar |title=Vote Now: Hyundai Goal Of The Tournament |publisher=FIFA |date=21 December 2022 |access-date=3 October 2023}}</ref>

Paik participated in the [[Football at the 2022 Asian Games – Men's tournament|2022 Asian Games]] as an overage player, and captained [[South Korea national under-23 football team|South Korean under-24 team]]. He scored three goals with his powerful shots in the competition, but was criticised for his mistakes responsible for conceding goals to opponents in the knockout stage. Nevertheless, he successfully finished his role, winning a gold medal.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://sports.news.naver.com/news?oid=076&aid=0004064463 |script-title=ko:"형 왜 이렇게 울어?…나 원래 눈물이 많아" 누구보다 여린 주장, 완장의 무게를 꿋꿋이 견뎠다[항저우ON] |publisher=[[Sports Chosun]] |language=ko |date=8 October 2023 |access-date=8 October 2023}}</ref>

In March 2024, Paik received his first senior call-up for a year, for home-and-away [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC second round#Group C|2026 World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Thailand national football team|Thailand]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/2024-03-11/sports/football/Paik-Seungho-rejoins-Korea-squad-as-Hwang-makes-some-changes/1999241 |title=Paik Seung-ho rejoins Korea squad as Hwang makes some changes |author=Paik Ji-hwan |newspaper=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]] |date=11 March 2024 |access-date=21 March 2024}}</ref> He started both matches, playing the whole of the home match, a 1–1 draw, and the first half of the away game, which South Korea won 3–0.<ref name="wf.net" />

